This paper focuses on image classification using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the impact of label granularity on CNN accuracy, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also propose a new metric to evaluate the effectiveness of fine-grain labeling, which could be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
